almost months pregnant hi i'm almost months along with our first baby my fiancee recently got laid off from a construction job where they laid all the new guys off lucky us huh well he has been asked to work with a guy to inspect tank trucks for about the same amount of money per hour but much more per week which is good now the draw back is that he will be out of state for either days per week every week or every other week with this job am i wrong to be upset that i will be all alone at our home with our new baby after she is born because he'll have to return back to work after weeks local work and i'll have to wake up every night with the baby to feed her and he'll be somewhere working in another state am i just being selfish or am i rightfully upset that he took this job because it was the first one that came to him and didn't wait and didn't consider what is going to be happening once his daughter is born anyone also i work full time at a wonderful job and will be getting paid maternity leave while i'm out but i just don't want him to have this job once she's born he could get another job somewhere but i don't know why he chose this one i don't want him to miss her smile or laugh or anything like that i don't want to feel like a single mother that gets money from the baby's father because he's not around and we both work out of nj but he has to leave nj to different states to work where they need him moving wouldn't solve that i would be highly upset too my boyfriend got laid off from a pretty well paying job and is currently job hunting if he gets a job where he will be out of town days a week every other week after our baby is born i will be furious i know that we will need the money especially while i'll be on leave but i want him to be in our baby's life as well i want him to see him her grow with me he can't do that on the road all the time plus you're going to need emotional support having a baby really does a number on your hormones and the last thing yo